2. App Functionality and Beta Disclaimer
2.1 Primary Purpose

The core function of the App is to help you track your daily steps and encourage you to reach individually set step goals.
You may connect and compare your step stats with friends on a leaderboard.
You may also link the App to certain gaming accounts so you can occasionally receive in-game rewards—such as items or boosts—if you achieve specific step goals or maintain streaks.
2.2 Individual Use and Friends Integration

The App is designed primarily for individual use but also allows you to connect with friends and compare step data.
There is currently no feature for posting user-generated content (e.g., photos, forum posts, comments).
2.3 Beta Status

The App is in an early closed beta stage. Features may change, and there may be bugs, errors, or interruptions in service. We reserve the right to modify or discontinue the App (or any part of it) without prior notice.
3. Third-Party Integrations and In-Game Rewards
3.1 Step Data Sources

The App retrieves step counts from third-party health platforms, such as Apple Health (iOS) and Google Health Connect (Android).
We do not guarantee the accuracy or reliability of data from these third-party sources.
3.2 Gaming Accounts and Rewards

In order to receive sporadic in-game rewards, you may connect your gaming account(s) to the App.
We are not responsible for any issues related to those third-party gaming platforms, including their own terms of service, reward availability, or the crediting of rewards to your gaming account.
Rewards are not guaranteed and may vary based on your location, your step activity, partnership arrangements, or other factors.
4. User Accounts and Data
4.1 Account Creation

To access certain features, including leaderboards and gaming rewards, you must register for an account.
You agree to provide accurate, current, and complete information as prompted by the App’s registration forms, and to keep that information updated.
4.2 Personal Data Collected

We currently collect your email address, daily step goal, and step count information (including your total step count since registering).
We do not collect sensitive health metrics such as heart rate, BMI, or medical conditions.
4.3 Data Storage & Security

Your data is stored on servers located in the EU. We use Supabase as our authentication and database provider.
Only senior technical members of our team have account permissions to access the database. We take reasonable security measures to protect your personal data; however, no security system is impenetrable.
4.4 Aggregated or Anonymized Data

We may share anonymized or aggregated data (e.g., total steps recorded across D2 users, top 10 user accounts’ stats) with potential investors, business partners, or for marketing purposes.
This does not include personally identifiable information.
5. Privacy and GDPR
5.1 GDPR Compliance

If you are located in the European Economic Area (EEA), you have certain rights under the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR), including the right to access, correct, and delete your data.
You can request deletion of your data from within the App or by contacting our Data Protection Officer at merlin.bergmann@karta.game.
5.2 Data Protection Officer

Our designated Data Protection Officer (DPO) is Merlin Bergmann, Product Director. You may direct any privacy-related inquiries to merlin.bergmann@karta.game.
For more details, please refer to our Privacy Policy (if available).

6. Health and Medical Disclaimer
6.1 No Medical Advice

The App only provides general fitness guidance by suggesting daily step goals (e.g., referencing the World Health Organization’s general guidelines).
We do not provide medical advice, diagnoses, treatment plans, or personalized nutrition or workout plans.
Always consult with a qualified healthcare professional before making decisions about your fitness activities.
6.2 Assumption of Risk

By using the App, you acknowledge that walking or other physical activities can carry inherent risks.
You assume all risks associated with your use of the App, including but not limited to potential injuries that may occur while walking or performing exercise.
6.3 Disclaimer of Liability

We are not liable for any injuries, health complications, or other damages you may suffer as a result of using the App or following any general fitness tips provided.
If you have specific medical concerns, please consult a healthcare professional.
